cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COM, cs.MM, cs.GT 

This paper discusses the use of aerial devices equipped with high-rate radio access capabilities to offer on-demand capacity boost for cellular networks. This topic falls under the category of networked and distributed systems, which is covered by cs.NI (Networked and Distributed Systems). The paper also discusses the use of licensed and license-exempt frequency bands, which is related to information theory and communication, covered by cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also models the market competition and cooperation behavior of aerial mmWave access suppliers, which is related to computational economics and computational social science, covered by cs.COM (Computational Economics and Computational Social Science). The paper also discusses the use of millimeter wave (mmWave) spectrum, which is related to multimedia and multimodal processing, covered by cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper analyzes the Nash equilibrium and profit balance in the market, which is related to game theory, covered by cs.GT (Game Theory).
